# Insurance-Management

The Project Contain Backend code for Insurance Management .

a. Clients: 

i.GET
/api/clients/get-all-clients: Fetch all clients. 

ii.GET
/api/clients/get-client-by-id/{id}: Fetch a specific client by ID. 

iii.POST
/api/clients/create-client: Create a new client.

iv.PUT
/api/clients/update-client-details/{id}: Update a client's information.

v.DELETE 
/api/clients/delete-client/{id}: Delete a client.


b. Insurance Policies:

i. GET
/api/policies/get-all-policies: Fetch all insurance policies.

ii. GET 
/api/policies/get-policy-by-id/{id}: Fetch a specific insurance policy by ID.

iii. POST
/api/policies/create-policy: Create a new insurance policy.

iv. PUT 
/api/policies/update-policy/{id}: Update an insurance policy.

v. DELETE
/api/policies/delete-policy/{id}: Delete an insurance policy.



c. Claims:

i. GET 
/api/claims/get-all-claims: Fetch all claims.

ii. GET 
/api/claims/get-claim-by-id/{id}: Fetch a specific claim by ID. 

iii. POST
/api/claims/create-claim: Create a new claim. 

iv. PUT 
/api/claims/update-claim/{id}: Update a claim's information.

v. DELETE 
/api/claims/delete-claim/{id}: Delete a claim.


# Steps to run the application locally :
1 :If you want to run the programme using h2 database then uncomment h2 dependancy from pom .xml and also uncomment h2 properties from application.properties you can do vise-versa if you want to use mysql .




# Discription Of project :

Using above apis we can create 3 module that are client ,claim and policy module .We can perform crud services on each module .
